## Rationale

Sieve GUI documentation includes the architecture, the IPC contract with the
daemon, the ADRs, and the HIPS UX design rationale. These are "trust artifacts" —
published so users can verify the security model before installing the signed
binary, not just take it on faith. They are deliberately kept open for study,
citation, and forking-for-research, while NonCommercial prevents them from being
repackaged as competitor material without permission.

